cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CC 

This paper deals with error control in random linear network coding, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also involves geometric properties and bounds, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the design of codes for error control, which is related to systems and control (cs.SI).
